# Action decisions (action)

These are individual utterance examples, so they don't lay out a whole-game strategy — the point here is to keep your action consistent with the line you have spoken, not to plan the board.

- **Make the action cash out your stated read.** Your vote/divine/attack should follow from what you argued in talk; a move that contradicts your public stance reads as a tell.
- **Commit cleanly — in 5 players there is little room to hedge.** Once your reasoning points somewhere, pick that target rather than a low-confidence detour; a wasted move can lock a bad next day.
- **Favor the move that reduces ambiguity fastest.** When your utterances have already narrowed the field, act on that narrowing rather than reopening everything.
